{
  "title": "Determinants",
  "summary": "Determinant of 2×2 and 3×3 matrices, minors, cofactors, Laplace expansion, and key properties including det(AB) = det(A)det(B).",
  "widget_type": "variables",
  "position": 3,
  "is_published": true,
  "content_html": "<style>\n.mat{display:inline-grid;border-left:3px solid #94a3b8;border-right:3px solid #94a3b8;padding:6px 12px;gap:4px 16px;border-radius:2px;background:#1e293b;vertical-align:middle}\n.mat td{text-align:right;font-family:monospace;font-size:.95em;color:#e2e8f0;min-width:24px}\n.mat-eq-block{background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin:12px 0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;gap:12px}\n.mat-named{display:inline-flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:4px}\n.mat-label{font-size:.78em;color:#64748b;font-family:monospace}\n.op{font-size:1.2em;font-weight:700;color:#94a3b8;padding:0 4px}\n.eq{font-size:1.2em;font-weight:700;color:#38bdf8;padding:0 4px}\n.formula-box{background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;margin:10px 0;font-family:monospace;font-size:1em;color:#f1f5f9;text-align:center}\n.note-box{background:#1a2e1a;border-left:4px solid #22c55e;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0;color:#bbf7d0;font-size:.93em}\n.def-box{background:#1e293b;border-left:4px solid #38bdf8;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0}\n.warn-box{background:#2d1f1f;border-left:4px solid #ef4444;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0;color:#fca5a5;font-size:.93em}\n.step-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:10px 0;font-family:monospace;font-size:.9em}\n.step-table td,.step-table th{border:1px solid #334155;padding:6px 10px;color:#e2e8f0}\n.step-table th{background:#1e293b;color:#7dd3fc}\n.step-table tr:nth-child(even) td{background:#0f172a}\n.sign-grid{display:inline-grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:4px;background:#1e293b;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:6px;padding:10px;font-family:monospace;font-size:1.1em;text-align:center}\n.sign-plus{color:#22c55e;font-weight:700}\n.sign-minus{color:#ef4444;font-weight:700}\n</style>\n<h3>1.4 Determinants</h3>\n<p>Every <strong>square</strong> matrix has an associated scalar called its <strong>determinant</strong>, written det(A) or |A|.</p>\n\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 1.17 (1×1):</strong> det([a₁₁]) = a₁₁</div>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 1.18 (2×2):</strong> det(A) = a₁₁a₂₂ − a₁₂a₂₁</div>\n\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\" style=\"display:inline-grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)\">\n      <tr><td>2</td><td>−9</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>8</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">= 2×8 − (−9×5) = 16 + 45 = <strong style=\"color:#22c55e\">61</strong></span>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Minors and Cofactors</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 1.19 — Minor M<sub>ij</sub>:</strong> Determinant obtained by deleting row i and column j.</div>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 1.20 — Cofactor C<sub>ij</sub>:</strong> C<sub>ij</sub> = (−1)<sup>i+j</sup> M<sub>ij</sub></div>\n\n<p>Sign pattern of (−1)<sup>i+j</sup>:</p>\n<div style=\"margin:8px 0\">\n  <div class=\"sign-grid\">\n    <span class=\"sign-plus\">+</span><span class=\"sign-minus\">−</span><span class=\"sign-plus\">+</span>\n    <span class=\"sign-minus\">−</span><span class=\"sign-plus\">+</span><span class=\"sign-minus\">−</span>\n    <span class=\"sign-plus\">+</span><span class=\"sign-minus\">−</span><span class=\"sign-plus\">+</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p>For A = [[1,2,3],[7,5,6],[4,8,9]]:</p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\" style=\"flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start\">\n  <div>M₁₁ = |5 6; 8 9| = 45−48 = <strong style=\"color:#f59e0b\">−3</strong> → C₁₁ = +M₁₁ = <strong style=\"color:#22c55e\">−3</strong></div>\n  <div>M₁₂ = |7 6; 4 9| = 63−24 = <strong style=\"color:#f59e0b\">39</strong> → C₁₂ = −M₁₂ = <strong style=\"color:#22c55e\">−39</strong></div>\n  <div>M₃₂ = |1 3; 7 6| = 6−21 = <strong style=\"color:#f59e0b\">−15</strong> → C₃₂ = −M₃₂ = <strong style=\"color:#22c55e\">15</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Laplace Expansion (3×3)</h4>\n<div class=\"formula-box\">det(A) = a₁₁C₁₁ + a₁₂C₁₂ + a₁₃C₁₃ &nbsp;(expand along any row or column)</div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.12:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\" style=\"flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:6px\">\n  <div style=\"font-family:monospace\">|4, 3, −1; 4, −7, 6; 1, 3, −9|</div>\n  <div>= 4·|−7,6;3,−9| − 3·|4,6;1,−9| + (−1)·|4,−7;1,3|</div>\n  <div>= 4(63−18) − 3(−36−6) − 1(12+7)</div>\n  <div>= 4(45) − 3(−42) − 19 = 180 + 126 − 19 = <strong style=\"color:#22c55e\">287</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"note-box\"><strong>Tip:</strong> When a row/column has zeros, expand along it to reduce computation. Example 1.14 uses column 3 (two zeros) for a shortcut.</div>\n\n<h4>Properties of Determinants</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>det(AB) = det(A) · det(B)</li>\n  <li>det(A<sup>T</sup>) = det(A)</li>\n  <li>det(I) = 1</li>\n  <li>det(λA) = λⁿ det(A) for n×n matrix A</li>\n  <li>Swapping two rows/columns: det(B) = −det(A)</li>\n  <li>Two identical rows/columns → det(A) = 0</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.13:</strong> A = [[2,−7,3],[1,5,−1],[4,0,5]] → det(A) = 53, det(A<sup>T</sup>) = 53 ✓</p>\n",
  "exercises": [
